 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFF0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uparsalianergvzek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ParsalianERGVzek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#000000>(8/4/01 7:21:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WAR!!!!!!!!!</span><hr size=1> Many of you may not know but earlier this year the ERG went to war with Illuvitae to defend the honor of our guild.  All those this was all well in good there is something that all of you have to remember about a guild war.<br>
<br>
-During a guildwar no one can be invited into the guild.  Which defeats the basic purpose of the EAG to recruit and train new members for the ERG.<br>
-Guildwars lead to lots of pvp.  Lots of PVP leads to faction hits.  After our last guildwar alot of us lost significant elf faction.  As you get higher lvls faction can become increasingly important.  Remember that as you engage in PVP.<br>
-Finally, the basic principle of ERG is the defense of the elven lands.  It is guild policy to &quot;immy heal&quot; ( which we are occasionally slammed for) and to defend those members of the light races that are being attacked by a pker.  If you are attacked by a member of BSL then fight back.  If you can heal, heal those that are being attacked by BSL.  Even erect an embargo against the BSL, which is again up to the Leader of EAG.  <br>
But remember a war is not always the best way to solve the problems betweeen guilds.  Remember to use your heads before your swords.  We aren't ogres and trolls.  We are the most civilized of the races and should act accordingly.  Good Luck and the proctection of Tunare upon all of you.<br>
Parsalian<br>
lvl 51 High Elf Mage<br>
